    "GTAN offer improved performance compared to both two-stage and single-stage technologies.",
    "Most of the proposed TAD models generate candidate proposals by subdividing them into frames or cutting them into video fragments.",
    "These methods are limited to local video information and cannot take advantage of video context relations.",
    "Based on traditional detection and linking strategies, in 2020 Li et al. (2020) proposed a single-stage model that can be trained end-to-end and a new coarse-to-fine action detector (CFAD).",
    "The CFAD uses two space-time action tubes, thick and thin."
